page_id: S4-X-04
platform_slice: Linux C4-10 linux-repo-connect
title: Create AreaMatrix Repository
description: Confirm Linux empty repository initialization before Core creates AreaMatrix metadata.
summary:
  - Folder: /home/you/AreaMatrix
  - Type: Local folder
  - Type: External drive
  - Type: Network mount
  - Type: Sync folder
  - Type: Unknown
  - Writable: Yes/No
copy:
  - AreaMatrix will create a .areamatrix folder here.
  - No existing files will be moved, deleted, renamed, or overwritten.
checks:
  - Folder is empty
  - Write permission available
  - Enough disk space: Core verifies metadata writes during creation.
states:
  checking: Checking folder...
  creating: Creating metadata...
  empty_path: Choose a folder first.
  ready: Ready to create .areamatrix metadata.
  failure: Try Again
actions:
  - Create Repository
  - Try Again
  - Choose Another Folder
  - Cancel
handoff:
  success: S4-LNX-02
safety:
  - The page calls validate_repo_path through LinuxRepositoryCoreBridge when opened.
  - The page calls init_repo through LinuxRepositoryCoreBridge only after Create Repository.
  - The page revalidates after init_repo and requires Core to detect .areamatrix metadata.
  - The page does not suggest sudo or chmod.
  - The page does not move, delete, rename, overwrite, adopt, import, reindex, or rescan user files.
